endo Drives '08 Industry Sales Past $21 Billion |author=James Brightman |publisher=[[GameDaily]] |date=January 15, 2009 |accessdate=January 17, 2009 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Place\n!Title\n!Platform\n!Publisher\n!Units sold\n|-\n|1\n|''[[Wii Play]]''\n|[[Wii]]\n|[[Nintendo]]\n|5.28 million\n|-\n|2\n|''[[Mario Kart Wii]]''\n|Wii\n|Nintendo\n|5.00 million\n|-\n|3\n|''[[Wii Fit]]''\n|Wii\n|Nintendo\n|4.53 million\n|-\n|4\n|''[[Super Smash Bros. Brawl]]''\n|Wii\n|Nintendo\n|4.17 million\n|-\n|5\n|''[[Grand Theft Auto IV]]''\n|[[Xbox 360|X360]]\n|[[Rockstar Games]]\n|3.29 million\n|-\n|6\n|''[[Call of Duty: World at War]]''\n|X360\n|[[Activision]]\n|2.75 million\n|-\n|7\n|''[[Gears of War 2]]''\n|X360\n|[[Microsoft]]\n|2.31 million\n|-\n|8\n|''Grand Theft Auto IV''\n|[[PlayStation 3|PS3]]\n|Rockstar Games\n|1.89 million\n|-\n|9\n|''[[Madden NFL 09]]''\n|X360\n|[[Electronic Arts]]\n|1.87 million\n|-\n|10\n|''[[Mario Kart DS]]''\n|[[Nintendo DS|NDS]]\n|Nintendo\n|1.65 million\n|}\n\n* Based on figures from the NPD Group via [[IGN]];<ref name=npdx360/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://xbox360.ign.com/articles/936/936932p1.html |title=Xbox 360 2008 Year in Review |author=IGN Xbox 360 Team |website=IGN |page=1 |date=December 12, 2008 |accessdate=January 3, 2009| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090101141334/http://xbox360.ign.com/articles/936/936932p1.html| archivedate= January 1, 2009 | url-status= live}}</ref> the games' publishers are listed in brackets:\n'''Best-selling video games of 2008 in the US (by platform)'''{{cref|a}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"width:825px; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!Place\n![[Nintendo DS|NDS]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ds.ign.com/articles/936/936935p2.html |title=Nintendo DS Year in Review 2008 |author=IGN Nintendo Team |website=IGN |date=December 9, 2008 |accessdate=January 3, 2009| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20081227181912/http://ds.ign.com/articles/936/936935p2.html| archivedate= December 27