 Coast]] || [[Brisbane Heat]]<br />[[Melbourne Stars]]\n|- style=\"text-align: center;\"\n| [[Ted Summerton Reserve]] || 7,500 || [[Moe, Victoria|Moe]] || [[Melbourne Stars]]\n|- style=\"text-align: center;\"\n| [[Coffs Harbour International Stadium]] || 20,000 || [[Coffs Harbour]] || [[Sydney Sixers]]\n|- style=\"text-align: center;\"\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"text-align: center;\"| '''Former Grounds'''\n|- style=\"text-align: center;\"\n| [[ANZ Stadium]] || 82,000 || [[Sydney]] || [[Sydney Thunder]] (2011\u20132014)\n|- style=\"text-align: center;\"\n| [[WACA Ground]] || 20,000 || [[Perth]] || [[Perth Scorchers]] (2011\u20132018)\n|-\n|}\n\n==Records and statistics==\n{{main|List of Big Bash League records and statistics}}\n[[File:Brisbane Heat vs Melbourne Stars T20 7.jpg|alt=|thumb|Chris Lynn, the leading run-scorer in BBL history]]\nHere is a list of Big Bash League records. All records are based on statistics at [[ESPNcricinfo|espncricinfo.com]].<ref>[http://stats.espncricinfo.com/big-bash-league-2014-15/engine/records/index.html?id=158;type=trophy Big Bash League/Records/Cup records] espncricinfo.com. Retrieved on 6 January 2015</ref> [[Brisbane Heat]] captain [[Chris Lynn]] currently holds the record of scoring most runs in the league.<ref name=\"most runs\" /> The record of taking most wickets in the league belongs to [[Ben Laughlin (cricketer)|Ben Laughlin]], who currently plays for [[Brisbane Heat]]. He has represented [[Hobart Hurricanes]] and [[Adelaide Strikers]] in the past, and has played a total of 88 BBL matches since 2011.<ref name=\"most wickets\" />\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\" style=\"color:#E4F300; background:#181A04;\"| Batting Records\n|-\n|Most runs\n|[[Brisbane Heat|{{color box|teal||}}]] [[Chris Lynn]]\n|2,332\n|-\n|[[batting average (cricket)|Highest average]]\n|[[Hobart Hurricanes|{{color box|purple}}]] [[D'Arcy Short]] \n|46.42\n|-\n|Highest score\n|[[Melbourne Stars|{{color box|#00B13F}}]] [[Marcus Stoinis]]\n|147* vs